OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FAutistic man to go home    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fafter 21 years in hospital 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, An autistic man who has been held in a 
OL,6, secure hospital for 21 years has been  
OL,7, told he can finally go home.           
OL,9,FTony Hickmott, 45, was sectioned after 
OL,10,Fhe had a mental health crisis in 2001, 
OL,11,Fand despite a long fight by his family,
OL,12,Fhe has not been released since.        
OL,14,FLast year, a judge criticised his      
OL,15,Fdetention, telling authorities to find 
OL,16,Fa home near his parents, in Brighton.  
OL,18,FA care team for Mr Hickmott is now     
OL,19,Fbeing assembled and he is expected in a
OL,20,Fnew home in his home town, next month. 
